<item>
            <title>[SPARK-3375] spark on yarn container allocation issues</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-3375</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It looks like if yarn doesn&apos;t get the containers immediately it stops asking for them and the yarn application hangs with never getting any executors.  This was introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/2169&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/2169&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
